  "prompt": "A shop was selling 3 chocolates for Re. 1 and if you return three wrappers you get 1 free. If so, how many chocolates can you get for Rs. 45?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1. First, let's calculate how many chocolates you can buy with Rs. 45\n   \u2022 3 chocolates cost Re. 1\n   \u2022 So, for Rs. 45, you can buy: 45 \u00d7 3 = 135 chocolates\n\n2. Now, let's count the free chocolates from wrappers\n   \u2022 For every 3 wrappers returned, you get 1 free chocolate\n   \u2022 Initially, you have 135 wrappers\n\n3. First round of free chocolates:\n   \u2022 135 \u00f7 3 = 45 free chocolates\n   \u2022 Now you have 45 more wrappers\n\n4. Second round of free chocolates:\n   \u2022 45 \u00f7 3 = 15 free chocolates\n   \u2022 Now you have 15 more wrappers\n\n5. Third round of free chocolates:\n   \u2022 15 \u00f7 3 = 5 free chocolates\n   \u2022 Now you have 5 more wrappers\n\n6. Fourth round of free chocolates:\n   \u2022 5 \u00f7 3 = 1 free chocolate\n   \u2022 Now you have 2 wrappers (not enough for more free chocolates)\n\n7. Total chocolates:\n   \u2022 Bought: 135\n   \u2022 Free: 45 + 15 + 5 + 1 = 66\n   \u2022 Total: 135 + 66 = 201 chocolates\n\nTherefore, you can get 201 chocolates for Rs. 45.",
